name: Handpainted RPG Icons Style LoRA
description:
• I extracted a LoRA file from my dreambooth custom model made for hand-painted object icons generations specificly. (REPO used for this: Kohya_ss)

  • For better understanding of how to use this model to get the best results visit the official model page.

  • The main advantage comparing to whole custom model is of course a light weight and possibility of using this LoRA file with any 1.5 based model. (I've tested it for a while and you can get some creative results - you have a taste of it in sample generations).

  • Outputs presented on this page are cherrypicked, but I've also did some random testing (you can check it here) and with a bit of workflow, experimenting and testing and a bit of luck you can get quiet interesting and expected results.

  • I strongly encourage you to test it with different models and a range of parameters and prompts (prompt editing is really helpful in this case).

In sample images beside overall presentation I focused also on showing the same subject but with different models and parameters.
